    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Tamás Nádasdy (Augsburg, 27 January 1551)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>The King is heading to Innsbruck from here for the first Sunday of Lent
                            to visit his daughters, then he will head on to Vienna for 1 March. Oláh
                            will head straight to Vienna, but he has not forgotten about Bratislava
                            either, he hopes an opportunity will arise. Márton Kecseti died in
                            poverty, he does not know how, but he does not think he was on the right
                            track. Some do not want to take on their share of the common tasks and
                            worries, but Oláh is not like that. The Queen is waiting for the scions,
                            while Oláh is waiting for an answer in the matter of the late Ferenc
                            Frangepán’s bishopric. </p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Spectabilis et Magnifice Domine et Frater Observandissime, servitiorum
                    meorum commendationem! </p>
                <p><persName>Maiestas regia</persName>, dominus noster clementissimus ad
                    Dominicam Invocavit<note type="critic">15 February.</note> ibit hinc
                        <placeName>Oenipontem</placeName>,<note type="critic">Innsbruck.</note>
                    magis filiarum suarum inivisendarum, quam aliarum rerum gratia, deinde recta
                        <placeName>Wiennam</placeName>, ad primum diem Martii. Ego nisi vi trahar,
                    recta hinc <placeName>Wiennam</placeName> Deo volente proficiscar. De
                        <placeName>Posonio</placeName> non obliviscar, nondum data est occasio bona.
                        <persName>Kechethi</persName><note type="critic">Márton Kecseti was Tamás
                        Szalaházy’s nephew, thanks to whom he became Bishop of Veszprém between 1527
                        and 1548. He then resigned from the bishopric and got married. He died on 13
                        January, 1551 in Bratislava, in miserable conditions, see <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Fazekas</hi> 2007, 33.</note> pauper mortuus est,
                    nescio, qualiter, ut audio, periculosum est <quote>aurum tangere
                        Tolosanum</quote><note type="quote">Gell. <hi rend="italic">Noct. Att.</hi>
                        3,9,7.</note><note type="critic">This proverb refers to a person who has bad
                        luck.</note> et <quote>equum Seianum.</quote><note type="quote">Gell. <hi
                            rend="italic">Noct. Att.</hi> 3,9.</note><note type="critic">According
                        to the proverb, anyone who possessed this horse died, together with their
                        entire family.</note> Mea sententia in officiis et aliis omnibus regni et
                    nostrorum omnium liberalitas inviolate semper observabitur, sed quid inter tot
                    unus? Alii ne digito quidem rem attingere aut volunt, aut ex corde cogitant, ut
                    commodi ita laboris et curae deberent esse participes. Ego nihil unquam me
                    praetermisisse memini, quod ad dignitatem regiam, simul etiam nostram libertatem
                    et permansionem pertinere fui arbitratus, neque deinceps et supplicando et
                    orando praetermittam. </p>
                <p>Surculos serenissima regia exspectat,<note type="critic">See Ep.
                        757.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15510106_1</ref> ego vero responsum de
                    specificatione rerum quondam fratris <persName>Francisci</persName>.<note
                        type="critic">Ferenc Frangepán, see Ep. 757. Cap.
                        1.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15510106_1</ref> Caesarea et regia maiestates
                    unacum regibus et principibus, laus Deo, bene valent. Dominationem Vestram
                    feliciter <del corresp="Olahus">valere opto</del> cum domina
                        <persName>coniuge</persName><note type="critic">Orsolya Kanizsai.</note> sua
                    carissima, domina mea valere opto, quibus me commendo.</p>
                <p>Ex <placeName>Augusta</placeName> 27. Ianuarii 1551.</p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="signature">Servitor et frater Agriensis etc. manu sua.</seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Spectabili et magnifico domino Thomae de Nadasd perpetuo comiti terrae
                    Fogaras, iudici curiae regiae maiestatis ac regni Hungariae supremo capitaneo
                    etc. domino et fratri observandissimo.</p>
            </div>
